commit_message: Updated multiple sample somatic variant calling.
configurator.py adds symlinks of raw data into project output folder.

- Fixed the checks controlling the bwa_align_ubam and markduplicates tasks.
- Parallelized the collect_wes_metrics task.
Updated backend configurations to minimize copying and hashing time
-Added checkpoints for the alignment and markdup tasks so that aligned samples could be skipped.
-Added markduplicates task to the variant calling pipeline. This separates the duplicate marking from the alignment job allowing more flexibility and efficiency.
Create symlinks using the relative path.
Disabled the gvcf array length check and changed the combine_genotype_gvcfs task to process any gvcf file because cromwell didn't like conditional array elements.
Changed backends to use cached file DB and call caching.
Added download links of VEP reports for the Mutect2 VCF files

- Updated slurm_singularity backend for using docker-submit and also avoiding DockerHub query limit.
- Added collect_variant_calling_metrics task.
- Made variant_calling_intervals optional for whole genome variant calling.

- Added a checkpoint for aligned but not dup-marked bam files.
- Integrated GATK's Mutect2 WDL pipeline.
- Updated backend configurations to run the pipeline on LustreCluster using Singularity
- Updated test files
Added GATK mutect2 WDL pipeline scripts

- Added optional exploratory columns to the reporting module
- Added dart_loader
- Added UMI aware duplication removal
Made necessary final adjustments for using singularity images to run germline variant calling.
Fixed a bug in generate_sample_vcfs task
Variant calling MultiQC module is modified to work with the current pipeline

- Added Ensembl VEP VCF annotation task
- Added annotated sample VCF generation
Added merge_combined_gvcfs task for generating cohort vcfs and gvcfs
Tasks bwa_align_ubam and collect_wes_metrics are implemented
